                <p>
                    To <strong>check company name availability UK</strong>, you must understand the rules Companies House applies. Selecting a name is more than branding — the UK has strict legal guidelines that govern every <strong>ltd company names register</strong> submission.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Firstly, your chosen name cannot be identical or "too like" an existing registered company. For example, if "Acme Services Ltd" already exists, Companies House will automatically reject "Acme Services UK Ltd" or "Acme Services Group Ltd" because they are legally considered identical under the "same as" rule.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Secondly, your chosen name cannot contain <strong>sensitive words or expressions</strong> unless you have special permission. Words like "British", "Royal", "Chartered", "Association", "Fund", and "Council" require specific documentation or regulatory approval.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Thirdly, even when Companies House approves your <strong>ltd company name</strong>, it may still infringe on an active trademark registered with the UK Intellectual Property Office (IPO). Always check trademarks alongside your company names search.
                </p>
