            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-5">

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How do I check company name availability in the UK?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Use our free <strong>company names search</strong> tool above. Enter your desired name and it instantly queries the live Companies House register — the same database used by official agents. Results show existing active and dissolved companies so you can assess whether your chosen name clears the "too-like" rule. Once clear, proceed to <a href="/register-a-limited-company-uk" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline font-bold">ltd company UK registration</a>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What does "check for company name availability" actually involve?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Checking for company name availability means running your proposed name through three tests: (1) the Companies House "same as" comparison against 5 million+ registered names, (2) the sensitive words list published under the Company, Limited Liability Partnership and Business (Names and Trading Disclosures) Regulations 2015, and (3) optionally, the UK IPO trademark database to rule out brand conflicts.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What are ltd company names and what are the rules?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Ltd company names are the official trading names for private limited companies registered at Companies House. Every valid UK ltd company name must end in "Limited" or "Ltd" (or Welsh equivalents), must not be "too like" an existing name, must not include restricted or sensitive words without approval, and must not imply a government connection or be offensive. Our <strong>company names search</strong> checks all of these automatically.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What does "Too Like" mean under UK company name rules?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A name is considered "too like" an existing name if it differs only by common words, punctuation, spacing, or generic suffixes. For example, "Plumbing London Ltd" is legally identical to "Plumbing London Group Ltd" or "Plumbing London UK Ltd". Companies House will automatically reject the duplicate. Our search highlights potential "too-like" matches so you can choose a truly distinctive name before your <strong>new ltd company registration</strong>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I reserve a company name without incorporating?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">No. Companies House does not permit name reservations. The only way to secure and protect a ltd company name is to actively incorporate it — either as a trading company or as a dormant shell for future use. Our same-day <strong>ltd company UK registration</strong> service can lock in your name within hours of you completing the online application.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What are sensitive words under UK ltd company names register rules?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Sensitive words are terms that imply national prestige, financial authority, or specific professional credentials. Examples include: Bank, Insurance, Trust, Charity, Royal, King, Queen, Windsor, and Chartered. To use these in your ltd company name, you must provide supporting authority letters when submitting your formation. Contact our team — we help navigate sensitive word approvals as part of our Enterprise formation packages.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How long does check company name availability UK take?</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Using our real-time company names search, the check takes under 5 seconds. Our tool queries the Companies House API directly, returning results on all active, dissolved, and protected names. Once you confirm your ltd company name is available, our formation process takes as little as 3–6 working hours for same-day registrations submitted before 3 PM UK time.</p>
                </div>

